<TITLE> Headless body found in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  Police recovered the decapitated body of a young man in the Sayadabad area of Dhaka on Sunday night. He has been named as Imtiaj Hossain Dipu, 22 from Maniknagar, a transport worker who was currently unemployed. Abdul Ali, a sub-inspector of Jatrabari Police Station told bdnews24.com that Dipu's badly burnt body was recovered at around 12am on barren land near Sayadabad's water purifying area. Dipu's brother Abul Kalam said that he had identified Dipu's body from his lungi and vest. Dipu, who had been missing since April 15 had recently helped the police arrest a terrorist named Shuman. The police suspect that this may be the reason behind his murder.. bd
